Class HashAutomaton<L,K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.jhoogland.jautomata.AbstractAutomaton<L,K>
      • net.jhoogland.jautomata.ExplicitAutomaton<L,K>
        • net.jhoogland.jautomata.HashAutomaton<L,K>
  • Type Parameters:
    L - label type
    K - weight type (Boolean for regular automata and Double for weighted automata)
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Automaton<L,K>, ReverselyAccessibleAutomaton<L,K>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EditableAutomaton, HashTransducer

    public class HashAutomaton<L,K>
extends ExplicitAutomaton<L,K>
    Implementation of Automaton that is backed up by HashMaps that contain information of states and transitions.
    Author:
    Jasper Hoogland
